## 3. Source Code and Intellectual Property

The software is provided only in compiled/binary form. No source code is provided or licensed.

All rights, title, and interest in and to the software remain the exclusive property of Typeflows. No rights are granted except those expressly stated in this License.

## 4. Post-Beta Licensing (v1.0.0+)

After beta, Typeflows will use a **repository-based licensing model**:

- **Always free**: Public repositories, open source projects (OSI-approved licenses), academic research, personal projects, and non-profit organizations
- **Commercial license required**: Private repositories in commercial contexts, commercial products or services, enterprise/self-hosted deployments

Registered commercial Beta users will receive advance notice and preferential pricing before commercial licensing begins.

Details will be published at: [typeflows.io/license](https://typeflows.io/license)

